resource.http://dev.llgc.org.uk/sas/full_text: <span style="color: #4d5156; font-family: Roboto, arial, sans-serif;">The Civilian Conservation Corps was a voluntary government work relief program that ran from 1933 to 1942 in the United States for unemployed, unmarried men ages 18–25 and eventually expanded to ages 17–28.
